{"id": 6218, "title": "Ticket #6218: Document condor_annex as of v080701.", "description": "<blockquote>\nWhether or not the 8.7.2 tickets for <code>condor_annex</code> will still be marked experimental, we need to (fully) document <code>condor_annex</code> as it will be released in v8.7.1 -- the <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://htcondor-wiki.cs.wisc.edu/index.cgi/wiki?p=HowToUseCondorAnnexWithOnDemandInstances\">getting started guide</a> on the Wiki is a good start, but, for example, doesn't even mention Spot Fleet.  We therefore need a usage manual.\n\n<p>We also need a man page for <code>condor_annex</code>; we should consider moving some of the usage information, particularly the \"expert mode\" options, from <code>condor_annex -help</code> to the man page.\n\n</p><p>This documentation may or may not also include technical details of the Annex implementation intended to make it easier for HTCondor administrators to customize their annexes, specifically including but not limited to the requirements for a disk image to be annex-compatible.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2017-Apr-06 11:35:47 by tlmiller:</em> <br/>\n\nThis documentation needs to includes tickets <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6147\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6147'); return false;\" title=\"Implement condor_annex -setup.\">#6147</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6149\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6149'); return false;\" title=\"Implement condor_annex -check-setup\">#6149</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6150\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6150'); return false;\" title=\"Improve output before annex attempt.\">#6150</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6155\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6155'); return false;\" title=\"Check collector connectivity before starting annex\">#6155</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6157\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6157'); return false;\" title=\"Allow/handle multiple simultaneous annexes\">#6157</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6184\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6184'); return false;\" title=\"Default annex should be restricted-use.\">#6184</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6196\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6196'); return false;\" title=\"Add (MayUseAWS == TRUE) to default START expression.\">#6196</a></span>, and <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6216\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6216'); return false;\" title=\"Spot Fleet -type annexes fail to join pool.\">#6216</a></span>.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Apr-21 16:07</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/67f7e731ad89a5bb44497bd8f87941b845e4eb14\">[50551]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6218\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6218'); return false;\" title=\"Document condor_annex as of v080701.\">#6218</a></span>) Grammar!  (By Todd L Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Apr-21 13:26</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/8d5ed10892a9e9120bcdf0